om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Tesla v. JPMorgan</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2014, JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. boug=
ht some warrants from Tesla Inc. JPMorgan paid Tesla something like=C2=A0$1=
30 million for the warrants, give or take, and those warrants=C2=A0gave it =
the option=C2=A0it to buy about 1.9 million shares of Tesla stock for about=
 $560.64 per share in the summer of 2021.[3] Then Tesla=E2=80=99s stock wen=
t up a lot, it did a 5-for-1 stock split, and it went up some more. By the =
summer of 2021, Tesla was trading at around $643 per share,[4] and JPMorgan=
 had warrants to buy about 9.5 million shares at about $112.12 per share.</=
p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In round numbers, if you can buy 9.5 million=
 shares for $112.12 each and sell them for $643 each, you will make about $=
5 billion of profit. Subtract the $130 million-ish of premium that JPMorgan=
 paid for the warrants in 2014, and you get a trade that made it $4.9 billi=
on of profit. Last November, JPMorgan sued Tesla demanding an extra $162.2 =
million due to a disagreement about a technical adjustment to the terms of =
the warrants.=C2=A0<em>This seems very petty!=C2=A0</em>JPMorgan was up $5 =
billion; let the other $162 million go.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now=
, to be clear, I am kidding. JPMorgan did not actually make $4.9=C2=A0billi=
on on these warrants. It did not buy the warrants as a bet that Tesla=E2=80=
=99s stock would go way up. That would have been a good bet! If it had made=
 that bet, it would be up by $4.9=C2=A0billion. It did not. It bought those=
 warrants as part of a complex hedging-and-tax-structuring transaction that=
 JPMorgan and three other banks did for Tesla in connection with a converti=
ble-bond deal. JPMorgan hedged the warrants =E2=80=94=C2=A0with the other p=
arts of the transaction, and/or by=C2=A0shorting some Tesla stock[5] =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0and its hedge went down as the warrant value went up. JPMorgan did=
 not make a bet on Tesla=E2=80=99s stock price that paid off to the tune of=
 $4.9 billion. JPMorgan=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>make a bet on Tesla=E2=80=99=
s=C2=A0<em>volatility=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=94=C2=A0the more volatile Tesla=E2=
=80=99s stock was over the last seven years, the more money JPMorgan would =
make on these warrants[6] =E2=80=94=C2=A0and=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>bet al=
so did pretty well, as Tesla has had a crazy last few years.</p><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">Nonetheless I am telling you this wrong thing because JPM=
organ=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>sue Tesla for that $162.2 million =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0we <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26482321.283=
628/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMTY=
vanBtb3JnYW4tZmlnaHRzLXRlc2xhLW92ZXItd2FycmFudHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDEyNTIyX01PTk=
VZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09M=
jIwMTI1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB47b5906a" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;"> discussed it in November</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0and because you=C2=A0<=
em>do=C2=A0</em>just necessarily look ridiculous coming in to court asking =
for $162.2 million extra on a trade where you=E2=80=99re already up $4.9 bi=
llion. =E2=80=9COh no we were hedged,=E2=80=9D you say, =E2=80=9Cour paper =
profit on that trade is not what we actually earned,=E2=80=9D and you are r=
ight, but come on man! It=E2=80=99s a bad look. After all, Tesla=C2=A0<em>d=
id=C2=A0</em>deliver $5 billion worth of stock to JPMorgan, and=C2=A0<em>it=
=C2=A0</em>wasn=E2=80=99t hedged. That=E2=80=99s just real value it paid ou=
t (in stock); asking for more is rough.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yes=
terday Tesla <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26482=
321.283628/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDEt=
MjQvdGVzbGEtZmlsZXMtY291bnRlcnN1aXQtYWdhaW5zdC1qcG1vcmdhbi1pbi13YXJyYW50cy1=
kaXNwdXRlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMjUyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3=
